- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper investigates leaderless consensus protocols in distributed systems. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper deals with robustness against Byzantine attacks. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper studies the impact of network topology on the consensus protocol. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper investigates the performance of the consensus protocol in noisy network infrastructures. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the computational complexity of the consensus protocol.
